<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_f383eba3-7c55-4413-9885-d4998cdbbc4f" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H8F1</sptc><title id="_9489e3b6-69c7-48a3-b00f-a62b98bf3d78">Livable housing design</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_74d30ee9-a77c-42e6-b438-dd7db6552288" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b01ecb8a-2856-41cc-849b-1176c2dfce9b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A dwelling should be designed such that it is—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_80a7528b-4e52-41c4-bbd5-1b1ca00e06ca">easy to enter; and</li><li id="_081dc6dc-b10d-4bbd-8e41-ba74b0649f27">easy to navigate in and around; and</li><li id="_131dfd1c-2b98-47df-9fe2-4225c7c9ed97">capable of easy and cost effective adaptation; and</li><li id="_a288dd46-f632-4de7-8f60-0c86b65d791e">responsive to the changing needs of occupants.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_6d5a21f8-8c31-4642-b4ef-8dad6c2c56a4"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>H8F1 only applies to a Class 1a building.</p></callout></clause>